{"id": "EUVD-2022-1274", "enisaUuid": "6748856e-b232-384c-8203-cad45e10ae18", "description": "Forge (also called `node-forge`) is a native implementation of Transport Layer Security in JavaScript. Prior to version 1.3.0, RSA PKCS#1 v1.5 signature verification code does not properly check `DigestInfo` for a proper ASN.1 structure. This can lead to successful verification with signatures that contain invalid structures but a valid digest. The issue has been addressed in `node-forge` version 1.3.0. There are currently no known workarounds.", "datePublished": "2022-03-18T13:30:14", "dateUpdated": "2025-04-23T18:46:17", "baseScore": 5.3, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:L/A:N", "references": ["https://github.com/digitalbazaar/forge/security/advisories/GHSA-2r2c-g63r-vccr", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-24773", "https://github.com/digitalbazaar/forge/commit/3f0b49a0573ef1bb7af7f5673c0cfebf00424df1", "https://github.com/digitalbazaar/forge/commit/bb822c02df0b61211836472e29b9790cc541cdb2", "https://github.com/digitalbazaar/forge", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2022:1681", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2022:1739", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2022:6156", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2022:6835"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-24773", "GHSA-2r2c-g63r-vccr"], "assigner": "GitHub_M", "epss": 0.1, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "c1ee1d4f-b67d-3757-8d6a-31aa059b319b", "product": {"name": "forge"}, "product_version": "< 1.3.0"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "46d65f6d-ec3f-3f71-ac95-ebab583334cb", "vendor": {"name": "digitalbazaar"}}], "isExploited": false}